  "title": "HYGIENE OFFICER",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role:</strong></p><p>We are looking for a detail-oriented and proactive <strong>Quality Assurance Executive</strong> to join our F&B team. You will play a vital role in ensuring that all our products and processes meet the highest standards of food safety, hygiene, and quality. If you are passionate about maintaining excellence in food production and compliance, we’d love to have you on our team!</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>food safety standards</strong> (HACCP, ISO 22000, NEA, SFA).</li><li>Conduct <strong>regular hygiene and safety audits</strong> across outlets and central kitchen.</li><li>Inspect <strong>raw materials, finished products, and storage conditions</strong>.</li><li>Monitor <strong>temperature records</strong>, pest control activities, and sanitation schedules.</li><li>Maintain <strong>QA documentation</strong>, audit reports, and corrective action records.</li><li>Collaborate with kitchen and operations teams to address quality issues.</li><li>Support and train staff on <strong>food safety and hygiene practices</strong>.</li><li>Prepare for and assist during <strong>SFA inspections and license renewals</strong>.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Food Science, Food Technology, or related field</strong>.</li><li>Minimum <strong>2–3 years of QA experience</strong> in the F&B or food manufacturing industry.</li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>HACCP, ISO 22000, and GMP standards</strong>.</li><li>Familiar with <strong>SFA/NEA regulations</strong>.</li><li>Meticulous, organized, and a good team player.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office.</li></ul><p><br /></p>",
